The paper deals with the classification of skin diseases using dermoscopic images, which involves image processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel multiple convolution neural network model, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of machine learning algorithms for classification also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category. The paper deals with image analysis, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia), and the use of ROC curves for evaluation suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as another possible category.
